On Wed, 23 Nov 2011, Mike wrote:

> throes of death rattles is to deflate the tires to compensate for the 1
> 1/2" excess height... about how much can one deflate a tire and move a
> short distance without mucking up the sidewalls?


Even fully flat wont hurt anything.  Worst it will do is unseat the bead, 
but even that isn't likely for a short straight roll.

(obviously -driving- on it flat is a different story....you'd be amazed at 
how much rubber can get chewed up inside the tire.)

